SUMMARY:Resource Drive for Exodus Refugee
DESCRIPTION:Month of April\nSupport New Neighbors: Resource Drive for Exodus Refugee Immigration\nJoin us in welcoming new families to our community by contributing to our April Resource Drive for Exodus Refugee. Your donations help provide essential everyday items to refugee families as they settle into life in the Bloomington area. Even small contributions can make a meaningful difference in helping families feel safe\, supported\, and at home. \nWhere to Drop Off Donations\nDonations can be dropped off: \n\nAt any of our public events in April\nAt the Lotus Firebay\n\nMonday\, Wednesday\, Friday: 12:00 PM – 1:00 PM *Unless there is a conflicting lotus event.\nThursdays: 3:00 PM – 6:00 PM\n\n\nQuestions or want to coordinate a drop-off?\nEmail Kirsten (KP) at associatedirector@lotusfest.org. \nItems Currently Needed\nToiletry Items (new only):\n\nShampoo / Conditioner\nHand Soap\nToothbrushes & Toothpaste\nDeodorant\nRazors\nToilet Paper\nSanitary Napkins\n\nHousehold Food Staples:\n\nDry Beans (pinto or black)\nRice\nMasa Flour\nSalt\nOil\nFufu\n\nGift Cards:\n\nGrocery stores (Walmart\, Kroger\, Aldi\, etc.)\nUber or Lyft\n\nItems We Cannot Accept\nTo ensure safety and storage capacity\, the following items cannot be accepted: \n\nUsed beds\, mattresses\, car seats\, cribs\, or pack & plays\nClothing (except outerwear)\nDesks or shelves (including bookshelves)\n\nTogether we can help new families build a foundation in our community. Thank you for supporting neighbors who are just beginning their journey here.
URL:https://www.lotusfest.org/event/resource-drive-for-exodus-refugee/
LOCATION:Lotus Firebay\, 105 S Rogers Street\, Bloomington\, IN\, 47404\, United States
CATEGORIES:Free Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://www.lotusfest.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Screenshot-2026-03-11-at-12.05.28-PM.webp
END:VEVENT
