DESCRIPTION:Thursday April 2nd\nEvent Time: 4:00 – 7:00 PM\nPerformance Time: TBD\nIU Fine Arts Plaza \nFree to the Public \nView the full event program \nAbout Eleanor & Dario\nEleanor Dubinsky (cello\, vocals) and Darío Acosta Teich (guitar) take audiences on a trip around the world with multilingual original songs and fresh interpretations of jazz and beloved classics in Spanish\, French\, Portuguese. Their elegant performances transcend genre and geography\, celebrating the beautiful diversity of our world. They serve as cultural ambassadors via the US Department of State Bureau of Educational and Cultural Affairs Arts Envoy program and African Regional Services. \n \n 
