SUMMARY:Lotus Lanterns
DESCRIPTION:Date: April 2\nTime: 4:00 to 7:00 p.m.\nLocation: IU First Thursday\nJoin us for a night of crafting as we explore the art of lantern making! Leading the project our OLP student Kate will be teaching and assisting you to make a beautiful Lotus Lantern out of recycled materials and paper. Bring your own plastic bottle or use one we’ve collected and share what makes you shine. \nLantern making is a globally recognized art. Representing hope\, guidance\, and the triumph of light of darkness.
URL:https://www.lotusfest.org/event/lotus-lanterns/
LOCATION:IN
CATEGORIES:Free Event
END:VEVENT
